# Futuristic UI — CSS & design tokens

When editing frontend CSS (including `globals.css`), keep the Electric Blue theme consistent and token-based.

## Tokens in `globals.css`

- **Colors:** Define all palette in `:root` only. Use `--color-accent` (Electric Blue) as the single primary accent; do not add other primary accent colors.
- **Electric Blue usage:** Reserve accent for primary CTA, focus states, and selected indicators. Glow (`--glow-accent`, `shadow-glow`) only for focus/primary — not for cards, badges, or decoration.
- **No hardcoded hex in component CSS.** If a color is needed in a stylesheet, add a token in `:root` and reference it (e.g. `rgb(var(--color-fg-muted))`), or use Tailwind token-based classes in components instead.

## Additive token changes

- New colors or spacing: add to `:root` with a clear name (`--color-*`, `--space-*`, `--radius-*`, `--duration-*`).
- Keep shadow/glow levels minimal (e.g. `--glow-accent` for focus only); avoid extra glow variables for decorative use.

## Quick reference

```css
/* ✅ GOOD — token in :root, use via var() */
:root {
  --color-accent: 99 102 241;
}
.focus-ring { box-shadow: var(--glow-accent); }

/* ❌ BAD — hardcoded hex outside :root */
.some-class { color: #6366f1; }
.card { box-shadow: 0 0 20px #6366f1; }
```
